-- Hwange Colliery of Zimbabwe Says Managing Director Moyo to Leave
-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 2012-07-21T09:44:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/hwange-colliery-of-zimbabwe-says-managing-director-moyo-to-leave.html
Hwange Colliery Ltd. of  Zimbabwe 
said Managing Director Fred Moyo will resign with effect from
September to pursue personal business interests.  Moyo has been with Hwange for more than 25 years and was
appointed to his present post in July 2007, the company said in
an e-mailed statement today.  Hwange exports coal to neighboring countries and India, and
provides the commodity for Zimbabwe Power Corp., a unit of
state-owned power utility Zesa Holdings (Pvt) Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
 gmarawanyika@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  